FBIS3-17199 "drsov057_b_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Two Russian Nuclear Subs Collide; Little Damage LD2403103094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1006 GMT 24 Mar 94 LD2403103094 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] [Text] Moscow March 24 TASS -- Two Russian nuclear submarines of the Northern Fleet collided on Wednesday in the Barents Sea while training joint manoeuvres and the press service of the Russian Navy qualified the incident as "a contact" of the U-boats. Nobody was injured, the armaments and equipment of the submarines is in proper order and the radioactive situation is normal, the press service said on Thursday adding that the subs returned to their base themselves. It was earlier reported that the "contact" resulted in inconsiderable damages which pose no danger to personnel and environment.
